"Uber uses your device's location services to make it easier to get a safe, reliable ride whenever you need one. Location data helps to improve our services, including pick-ups, navigation, customer support and more.
If you're using an Android device, and location collection is enabled, we may collect location information from the time you open the Uber app until your trip ends or is cancelled. This includes when your app is not visible on screen.
If you disable location collection, you can still use the Uber app, but you'll need to enter your pick-up and drop-off locations manually.
You can manage location settings on your device. To do this, open your device's Settings, find your location permissions for Uber, and toggle location 'on' or 'off'.
We treat your location information consistently with our Privacy Policy."
